Confirming the Effective TV and Movie Ratings

</div>

</div>

<div class="content" v-15d7e6ba="" v-60225a94="">

## <a href="/documentation/managedsettings/managedsettingsstore/$effectivemaximumtvshowrating#discussion" class="header-anchor" data-v-5e9b845c="" data-after-text="in page link">Discussion<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="svg-icon link-icon icon" /></a>

An authorized app can use the Family Controls framework to apply a <a href="/documentation/managedsettings/mediasettings/maximumtvshowrating-swift.property" class="inline-link"><code data-v-88c637be="">maximumTVShowRating</code></a> to the device. If no `maximumTVShowRating` settings are active, then the value of this property is the default value of <a href="/documentation/managedsettings/mediasettings/maximumtvshowrating-swift.type.property" class="inline-link"><code data-v-88c637be="">maximumTVShowRating</code></a>. The system publishes changes dynamically.

</div>
